        {
          "number": 4,
          "slidetitle": "Fabricated Outputs and False Results",
          "subtitle": "When AI Invents Plausible but False Data",
          "slidecontent": "• AI tools can generate statistics, citations, and findings that look credible but are entirely made up\n• Known as \"hallucination\" in technical terms\n• A fabricated reference may include a real journal name, a plausible author, and a convincing title, yet the paper does not exist\n• No built-in fact-checker\n• Researchers who paste AI output directly into reports risk publishing false evidence without realising it\n• The problem is especially dangerous in fields where a single incorrect figure can mislead further studies"
        },
        {
