          "slidetitle": "Spotting Fabricated AI Outputs",
          "subtitle": "Recognising hallucinations and false citations",
          "slidecontent": "• AI tools sometimes invent plausible-sounding citations that do not actually exist\n• Always verify references independently using a database such as PubMed or Google Scholar\n• Fabricated outputs often look convincing\n• Watch for vague author names, incorrect journal titles, or page numbers that do not match\n• Statistics and data figures generated by AI should never be used without checking the original source\n• A confident tone from an AI tool is not evidence of accuracy"
        },
        {
